dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. The dataset is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.

dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset similar to CIFAR-10 but contains 100 classes with 600 images each. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100
